[new]
Since I'm not going to edit the data files directly, I would have to do what anybody has to do:
[http://www.oddmuse.org/cgi-bin/oddmuse/Automatic_Posting_and_Uploading automatic posting and uploading]
using scripts (written in Perl or Python) such as *wikiput* or *wikiappend* (and I haven't used them in a long time).
There's also [http://www.oddmuse.org/cgi-bin/oddmuse/Download_Using_Curl_And_Caching downloading using curl]
for some information. You can also post using curl: You need to supply the following parameters:

: title: The_Page_Title
: text: the page text
: uihnscuskc: 1 (to bypass the Turing test-wannabe)

I think that should be enough. -- AlexSchroeder

[new]
Very nice -- didn't know about these tools. I will do this but probably not today. -- JonasBernoulli

[new]
Heh, did it! For future reference:

{{{
for f in AdamSpiers Adrian_Aichner AhmetUsal ...; do
    echo $f
    curl http://emacswiki.org/cgi-bin/wiki/raw/$f > $f;
    echo "----" >> $f;
    echo "CategoryHomepage" >> $f;
    curl -F recent_edit=on -F summary=CategoryHomepage -F title=$f \
         -F "text=<$f" -F uihnscuskc=1 -F username=AlexSchroeder \
         http://emacswiki.org/cgi-bin/wiki
    sleep 5;
done
}}}

-- AlexSchroeder

